711840f-b.title: Manhattan: 26th Street (West) - 10th Avenue
711840f-b.text:
West 26th Street, north side, east of Tenth Avenue, showing a
parking 1ot adjacent to a tenement, No. 461,which partially appears
on the left.
In the background, across the roof tops, one sees the mooring
mast atop the Enpire State Bldg.
Auaust 4, 1938.
Views 1 and 2
J. L. Sperr

710518f-a.title: Manhattan: 10th Avenue - 26th Street (West)
710518f-a.text:
Tenth Avenue, south across W. 29th Street. In the background
are the London Terrace buildings at 23rd Street and the R. C. Williams
Company warehouse (Royal Scarlet Brand) at 25th and 26th Street. The
former are east of the Avenue and the latter on the west.
August 25, 1940
Views 1,2
P. L. Sperr
Tenth Avenue, west side, at 29th Street, looking northward,
same view as above from another angle.
P. L. Sperr  AuEust 25, 1940
